message.content:
Here's the SVG code that draws all the specified shapes in the given order:

```svg
<svg viewBox="0 0 400 200" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
  <!-- Points -->
  <circle cx="0" cy="0" r="2" fill="black"/>
  <circle cx="100" cy="50" r="2" fill="black"/>
  <circle cx="200" cy="100" r="2" fill="black"/>
  <circle cx="300" cy="150" r="2" fill="black"/>
  <circle cx="400" cy="200" r="2" fill="black"/>

  <!-- Diagonal line -->
  <line x1="0" y1="0" x2="400" y2="200" stroke="black"/>

  <!-- Circles -->
  <circle cx="100" cy="50" r="50" fill="none" stroke="black"/>
  <circle cx="200" cy="100" r="100" fill="none" stroke="black"/>
  <circle cx="300" cy="150" r="150" fill="none" stroke="black"/>

  <!-- Triangle -->
  <polygon points="0,0 100,50 200,100" fill="none" stroke="black"/>

  <!-- Rectangles -->
  <polygon points="0,0 100,50 200,100 300,150" fill="none" stroke="black"/>
  <polygon points="100,50 200,100 300,150 400,200" fill="none" stroke="black"/>

  <!-- Complex polygon with holes -->
  <path d="M 0,0 L 100,50 200,100 300,150 400,200 Z
           M 50,25 L 150,75 250,125 350,175 Z
           M 75,37 L 175,87 275,137 375,187 Z"
        fill="lightgray" stroke="black" fill-rule="evenodd"/>
</svg>
```

This SVG features:
1. Five small black points at specified coordinates
2. A diagonal black line connecting (0,0) to (400,200)
3. Three concentric circles with increasing radii
4. A triangle connecting the first three points
5. Two quadrilaterals in stepped patterns
6. A complex polygon with the main shape following the diagonal pattern and two sets of inner holes

The elements are organized in z-order according to the requested sequence, using transparent fill for most shapes and lightgray fill for the final polygon to highlight its complex structure. The viewBox preserves aspect ratio while maintaining all coordinates proportional.
